6
00:00:13,732 --> 00:00:15,732
The culprit wounded the then,

7
00:00:15,732 --> 00:00:17,432
assistant inspector Matsumoto in the left eye.

8
00:00:18,832 --> 00:00:20,032
The valid date for the incident that happened

9
00:00:20,032 --> 00:00:22,132
20 years ago had already expired,

10
00:00:22,132 --> 00:00:24,032
And, there are only three more days to go

11
00:00:24,032 --> 00:00:27,232
before the incident that happened 15 years will also expire.

12
00:00:27,232 --> 00:00:29,832
There are two clues leading to the culprit.

13
00:00:29,832 --> 00:00:31,832
One is the straight-lined scar

14
00:00:31,832 --> 00:00:33,132
that Superintendent Matsumoto had left

15
00:00:33,132 --> 00:00:35,432
on the back of the culprit.

16
00:00:35,432 --> 00:00:37,632
The other is the whistling.

17
00:00:37,632 --> 00:00:42,132
He kept whistling a song that was popular 20 years ago.

18
00:00:43,132 --> 00:00:46,132
While Officer Takagi and the others were doing their best investigating,

19
00:00:46,132 --> 00:00:49,032
criminal psychologist, Mr. Douji Hiramune

20
00:00:49,032 --> 00:00:51,132
continued to make provoking statements

21
00:00:51,132 --> 00:00:54,232
to the culprit on air and in magazines.

22
00:00:54,232 --> 00:00:55,832
And...

23
00:00:55,832 --> 00:00:59,632
I passed a weird guy at the entrance.

24
00:00:59,632 --> 00:01:02,132
He was wearing an off-season long coat

25
00:01:02,132 --> 00:01:04,032
and whistling a tune.

26
00:01:05,332 --> 00:01:09,932
Did the serial killer really come?

27
00:01:12,032 --> 00:01:14,132
Love is eternal, labyrinths are mysterious.

28
00:01:14,132 --> 00:01:16,432
Saturday nights are for mystery.

29
00:01:16,432 --> 00:01:18,432
You're not your usual self, Officer Takagi.

30
00:01:18,432 --> 00:01:20,532
Heading straight to arrest the culprit?

31
00:01:20,532 --> 00:01:22,132
He sees through the one and only truth.

32
00:01:22,132 --> 00:01:24,032
A child in appearance with the I.Q. of an adult.

33
00:01:24,032 --> 00:01:26,032
No case is left unsolved with Detective Conan.

34
00:03:08,359 --> 00:03:13,459
"A New Scar and the Whistling Man"

35
00:03:14,859 --> 00:03:16,359
Really, Conan?

36
00:03:16,359 --> 00:03:17,959
Is it true that there is a possibility

37
00:03:17,959 --> 00:03:20,859
that the serial killer came to that condo?

38
00:03:20,859 --> 00:03:23,059
I heard that the criminal psychologist

39
00:03:23,059 --> 00:03:25,259
named Mr. Hiramune who was on TV a while ago

40
00:03:25,259 --> 00:03:28,059
"Hiramune" -lives in this condo.

41
00:03:28,059 --> 00:03:31,459
I'm going over to that person's place!

42
00:03:31,459 --> 00:03:32,859
Wait, Conan!

43
00:03:32,859 --> 00:03:34,359
Conan!

44
00:03:34,359 --> 00:03:36,159
Officer Chiba, will you go get the car.

45
00:03:36,159 --> 00:03:37,159
Yes.

46
00:03:37,159 --> 00:03:39,659
"Hiramune"

47
00:03:43,059 --> 00:03:44,459
There's no answer.

48
00:03:51,459 --> 00:03:52,559
It's open.

49
00:03:57,759 --> 00:03:59,259
Mr. Hiramune.

50
00:03:59,259 --> 00:04:00,459
Are you there?

51
00:04:03,559 --> 00:04:04,659
Mr. Hiramune.

52
00:04:06,859 --> 00:04:08,259
Mr. Hiramune.

53
00:04:11,159 --> 00:04:14,259
No good.

54
00:04:14,259 --> 00:04:18,659
There's blood on his Polo shirt?

55
00:04:18,659 --> 00:04:20,059
"Z"?

56
00:04:21,759 --> 00:04:24,559
The man who was murdered is criminal psychologist,

57
00:04:24,559 --> 00:04:27,259
Mr. Douji Hiramune, age 41.

58
00:04:27,259 --> 00:04:30,559
The murder weapon is the fruit knife

59
00:04:30,559 --> 00:04:33,859
that was in the kitchen here.

60
00:04:33,859 --> 00:04:35,759
There's a trace of a stun gun

61
00:04:35,759 --> 00:04:37,559
having been stuck out at the back of his neck.

62
00:04:37,559 --> 00:04:39,159
Judging from the alphabet that is carved on his back,

63
00:04:39,159 --> 00:04:41,259
this is likely the doings

64
00:04:41,259 --> 00:04:43,159
of the same serial killer of all the other cases.

65
00:04:44,359 --> 00:04:47,259
But the letter this time is "Z".

66
00:04:47,259 --> 00:04:50,659
I also thought that the next letter would be "N".

67
00:04:50,659 --> 00:04:52,559
According to the investigation reports

68
00:04:52,559 --> 00:04:58,059
the letters in the order of E, S, and W

69
00:04:58,059 --> 00:04:59,859
were carved on the bodies of the victims.

70
00:04:59,859 --> 00:05:00,959
Therefore, if the next letter is "N",

71
00:05:00,959 --> 00:05:03,659
it would complete the four cardinal directions.

72
00:05:03,659 --> 00:05:06,459
But, if the letters symbolize the four cardinal directions,

73
00:05:06,459 --> 00:05:10,059
it would be east, west, south, north.

74
00:05:10,059 --> 00:05:13,859
So the order of the letters should be E, W, S, N.

75
00:05:13,859 --> 00:05:17,459
Well, it's for certain that this is not the doings of a copycat.

76
00:05:17,459 --> 00:05:20,459
It hasn't been publicized that letters

77
00:05:20,459 --> 00:05:22,359
are carved on the bodies of the victims and besides,

78
00:05:22,359 --> 00:05:23,959
Conan's friend seems to have mentioned

79
00:05:23,959 --> 00:05:27,859
passing a man at the entrance who was whistling.

80
00:05:27,859 --> 00:05:30,959
But, no matter if he knew about the case,

81
00:05:30,959 --> 00:05:34,259
to think that after hearing from his friend

82
00:05:34,259 --> 00:05:35,959
about a man who was whistling

83
00:05:35,959 --> 00:05:38,159
it's amazing that you would sense that Mr. Hiramune

84
00:05:38,159 --> 00:05:39,759
who had been bad-mouthing the killer would be in danger,

85
00:05:39,759 --> 00:05:42,559
and run in here first thing.

86
00:05:42,559 --> 00:05:46,859
You're running around like a full fledged detective as always, Conan.

87
00:05:48,159 --> 00:05:52,259
Did he bad-mouth the killer that badly?

88
00:05:52,259 --> 00:05:53,359
Yes, sir.

89
00:05:53,359 --> 00:05:55,459
He would say things like the killer is trembling

90
00:05:55,459 --> 00:05:57,859
waiting for his term to expire.

91
00:05:57,859 --> 00:06:00,959
Or, if he's got the guts, to come out and appear before him.

92
00:06:00,959 --> 00:06:02,659
It's as if he's provoking the killer.

93
00:06:02,659 --> 00:06:03,859
Yes, sir.

94
00:06:03,859 --> 00:06:06,659
Mr. Hiramatsu also repeatedly bashed the killer

95
00:06:06,659 --> 00:06:09,059
likewise in the papers and weekly magazines too.

96
00:06:09,059 --> 00:06:12,859
It seems that Mr. Hiramune rushed home

97
00:06:12,859 --> 00:06:14,859
after finishing his live appearance at a TV station.

98
00:06:14,859 --> 00:06:18,459
He seems to have waiting for an acquaintance to come to his place.

99
00:06:18,459 --> 00:06:20,359
I guess we could deem that acquaintance

100
00:06:20,359 --> 00:06:21,459
of his to be a suspect.

101
00:06:21,459 --> 00:06:25,259
He could be someone connected with copy machines or something.

102
00:06:26,259 --> 00:06:30,359
See, under Mr. Hiramune's left hand.

103
00:06:30,359 --> 00:06:34,759
There's blood on the Ctrl key and C key.

104
00:06:34,759 --> 00:06:36,459
If you press these two key,

105
00:06:36,459 --> 00:06:38,059
you can copy something right?

106
00:06:39,059 --> 00:06:40,759
That's true.

107
00:06:40,759 --> 00:06:44,159
Maybe the killer left it there deliberately.

108
00:06:44,159 --> 00:06:48,559
But, there's no blood on his left hand, right?

109
00:06:48,559 --> 00:06:49,659
True.

110
00:06:49,659 --> 00:06:52,759
Blood for some reason is only on his right hand

111
00:06:52,759 --> 00:06:54,159
where he's holding the mouse.

112
00:06:54,159 --> 00:06:57,559
Which means that blood was put on the key with his right hand,

113
00:06:57,559 --> 00:07:00,759
which after he went out of his way to cover it with his left hand, right?

114
00:07:00,759 --> 00:07:03,259
If the killer left it deliberately,

115
00:07:03,259 --> 00:07:05,159
do you think he would do something like this?

116
00:07:05,159 --> 00:07:06,559
Right.

117
00:07:06,559 --> 00:07:09,459
I think he would leave something that is more conspicuous behind.

118
00:07:09,459 --> 00:07:11,859
He didn't put the blood on with his left hand

119
00:07:11,859 --> 00:07:14,459
to make it look like it wasn't a coincidence.

120
00:07:14,459 --> 00:07:17,459
He hid it with his left hand

121
00:07:17,459 --> 00:07:19,659
because he didn't want to show it to the killer.

122
00:07:19,659 --> 00:07:22,359
In other words, Mr. Hiramune,

123
00:07:22,359 --> 00:07:27,159
at the moment of his death left a dying message.

124
00:07:28,359 --> 00:07:31,259
There is a copy machine in this room but...

125
00:07:31,259 --> 00:07:32,859
I checked a while ago,

126
00:07:32,859 --> 00:07:35,059
but nothing looked strange.

127
00:07:35,059 --> 00:07:37,759
Could it be a coy band or something?

128
00:07:37,759 --> 00:07:40,159
The tune the suspect was whistling was a song

129
00:07:40,159 --> 00:07:42,859
that was popular 20 years ago, right?

130
00:07:42,859 --> 00:07:45,559
It could be a band that is covering that tune.

131
00:07:45,559 --> 00:07:48,659
There are a million bands that would doing something like that.

132
00:07:48,659 --> 00:07:49,759
Superintendent Matsumoto.

133
00:07:49,759 --> 00:07:50,759
-Sir. -Sir.

134
00:07:50,759 --> 00:07:53,959
It was the song of the times back then.

135
00:07:53,959 --> 00:07:59,859
Well, it seems to hold a deep meaning for the killer though.

136
00:07:59,859 --> 00:08:01,459
Deep meaning?

137
00:08:01,459 --> 00:08:03,859
Do you know that 20 years ago

138
00:08:03,859 --> 00:08:06,959
Morimura went to question the person

139
00:08:06,959 --> 00:08:08,859
in a suspicious car that he frequently saw

140
00:08:08,859 --> 00:08:12,859
and died on duty when he was run over by that car?

141
00:08:13,859 --> 00:08:16,859
It seems that the man was whistling that tune

142
00:08:16,859 --> 00:08:19,959
even as Morimura approached the car.

143
00:08:19,959 --> 00:08:22,559
And the man was in tears.

144
00:08:22,559 --> 00:08:24,259
Tears?

145
00:08:24,259 --> 00:08:25,459
Okay.

146
00:08:25,459 --> 00:08:28,259
Sato and Chiba, go question people in this vicinity.

147
00:08:28,259 --> 00:08:29,259
-Yes, sir. -Yes, sir.

148
00:08:29,259 --> 00:08:31,459
Shiratori, keep the copy machine in mind

149
00:08:31,459 --> 00:08:34,359
and go check around Mr. HIramune once more.

150
00:08:34,359 --> 00:08:35,759
That's just what I plan to do.

151
00:08:35,759 --> 00:08:37,659
Takagi, just to be safe,

152
00:08:37,659 --> 00:08:39,059
go meet the bereaved families of the victims

153
00:08:39,059 --> 00:08:40,259
of the past three cases,

154
00:08:40,259 --> 00:08:42,959
and check to see if they had any kind of connection

155
00:08:42,959 --> 00:08:43,959
with Mr. Hiramune.

156
00:08:43,959 --> 00:08:46,059
Yes, sir! Roger!

157
00:08:49,259 --> 00:08:50,659
So enthusiastic.

158
00:08:52,959 --> 00:08:55,759
Maybe it worked a bit too effectively.

159
00:08:57,959 --> 00:09:01,359
The murder case that had only three days to go before expiration.

160
00:09:01,359 --> 00:09:03,459
Now with a new murder committed by the same killer,

161
00:09:03,459 --> 00:09:06,059
has 15 more years to go before expiration.

162
00:09:06,059 --> 00:09:07,159
Oh no.

163
00:09:07,159 --> 00:09:09,759
The Criminal Procedure Act was revised

164
00:09:09,759 --> 00:09:14,159
and the new expiration date for murders cases is 25 years.

165
00:09:14,159 --> 00:09:15,959
If we can only nab this killer

166
00:09:15,959 --> 00:09:18,959
within the 25 years we from now.

167
00:09:21,459 --> 00:09:24,059
I get to go with Ms. Sato, just the two of us...

168
00:09:24,059 --> 00:09:25,759
to the hot spring!

169
00:09:27,059 --> 00:09:28,259
I see.

170
00:09:29,259 --> 00:09:32,759
That's why he's more out to get than always.

171
00:09:32,759 --> 00:09:34,359
His motive's impure.

172
00:09:34,359 --> 00:09:36,259
A hot spring, how nice.

173
00:09:36,259 --> 00:09:40,059
Take us with you too.

174
00:09:40,059 --> 00:09:42,559
Why are you guys in this car?

175
00:09:43,559 --> 00:09:47,059
You let us on yourself!

176
00:09:47,059 --> 00:09:49,659
In the parking lot, we asked you, "Where are you going?"

177
00:09:49,659 --> 00:09:51,859
