178
00:09:51,859 --> 00:09:54,659
You didn't look like you were all there, though.

179
00:09:56,959 --> 00:09:58,859
Well... my head was filled with thoughts about the hot spring.

180
00:09:58,859 --> 00:10:02,259
No, I mean the case so...

181
00:10:02,259 --> 00:10:04,459
And what do you intend to do?

182
00:10:04,459 --> 00:10:06,959
Are you going to take us with you?

183
00:10:06,959 --> 00:10:08,559
Or, are you going to let us down?

184
00:10:08,559 --> 00:10:11,359
Of course I'm going to let you all down.

185
00:10:11,359 --> 00:10:15,459
But Ayumi and Ai passed by the killer, you know.

186
00:10:15,459 --> 00:10:20,259
But, I'm headed for the houses of the bereaved families of the victims

187
00:10:20,259 --> 00:10:22,259
of the cases 20 and 15 years ago.

188
00:10:22,259 --> 00:10:27,059
But, I heard them say on TV that the bereaved families

189
00:10:27,059 --> 00:10:28,559
are also being suspected as suspects.

190
00:10:28,559 --> 00:10:30,759
True, but...

191
00:10:30,759 --> 00:10:33,759
Well, if you intend to wait 25 years

192
00:10:33,759 --> 00:10:36,259
for Officer Sato who'll turn 50

193
00:10:36,259 --> 00:10:39,559
and become a super over the hill mature woman,

194
00:10:39,559 --> 00:10:41,259
you can try handling everything alone.

195
00:10:42,259 --> 00:10:43,859
-Super over the hill mature. -Super over the hill mature.

196
00:10:43,859 --> 00:10:45,659
She's just great now though.

197
00:10:45,659 --> 00:10:47,359
She's beautiful too!

198
00:10:47,359 --> 00:10:49,359
She sure is a buy, I'd say.

199
00:10:53,659 --> 00:10:57,059
Listen, the only one who gets out of the car is Conan.

200
00:10:57,059 --> 00:11:00,659
The rest of you stay put in the car, all right?

201
00:11:00,659 --> 00:11:01,959
-Yes, sir. -Yes, sir...

202
00:11:04,759 --> 00:11:07,559
The person we're about to meet now

203
00:11:07,559 --> 00:11:10,659
is the wife of Mr. Tsuguharu Bokawa, a doctor,

204
00:11:10,659 --> 00:11:14,059
the first victim who was killed 20 years ago, right?

205
00:11:14,059 --> 00:11:18,159
"Bokawa General Hospital" -Yes. Mr. Bokawa was the head of a hospital,

206
00:11:18,159 --> 00:11:22,259
and his wife Maiko inherited a great amount of estate,

207
00:11:22,259 --> 00:11:25,959
so she was taken up as a suspect.

208
00:11:25,959 --> 00:11:28,459
But, no concrete evidence

209
00:11:28,459 --> 00:11:29,859
was found nor did she have anything connecting her

210
00:11:29,859 --> 00:11:33,459
with Mr. Mugita, the second victim who was killed.

211
00:11:36,459 --> 00:11:40,059
Yes. I know this person.

212
00:11:40,059 --> 00:11:41,859
He's Mr. Hiramune, the criminal psychologist

213
00:11:41,859 --> 00:11:45,459
"Maiko Bokawa (62)" -that appears on TV frequently, isn't he?

214
00:11:45,459 --> 00:11:47,659
What about him?

215
00:11:47,659 --> 00:11:51,659
He was found killed in his condo just a while ago.

216
00:11:51,659 --> 00:11:56,759
Most probably by the same killer who killed your husband 20 years ago.

217
00:11:56,759 --> 00:11:58,659
My, how frightening.

218
00:11:58,659 --> 00:12:00,559
So, I'm wondering if your husband

219
00:12:00,559 --> 00:12:05,459
was in any way connected to Mr. Hiramune.

220
00:12:05,459 --> 00:12:08,859
I wonder how old is Mr. Hiramune?

221
00:12:08,859 --> 00:12:10,759
41 years old.

222
00:12:10,759 --> 00:12:13,759
Then, 20 years ago he was 21 years old

223
00:12:13,759 --> 00:12:16,859
and my husband died when he was 50.

224
00:12:16,859 --> 00:12:20,959
It's hard for me to believe that they were connected in any way.

225
00:12:20,959 --> 00:12:22,559
I see.

226
00:12:22,559 --> 00:12:25,659
Did he ever meet anyone in secret?

227
00:12:26,659 --> 00:12:29,059
Who is he, this boy?

228
00:12:29,059 --> 00:12:33,159
I'm watching the officer on duty for social studies.

229
00:12:33,159 --> 00:12:35,759
Oh, is that so.

230
00:12:35,759 --> 00:12:38,859
But, it's true that he used to frequently drink

231
00:12:38,859 --> 00:12:41,759
with someone on Saturday nights.

232
00:12:41,759 --> 00:12:44,259
Do you have any idea who it was?

233
00:12:44,259 --> 00:12:45,659
No.

234
00:12:45,659 --> 00:12:49,559
Only, there was a time when he came home totally wasted back then.

235
00:12:49,559 --> 00:12:54,659
"Darn! How dare he call me cry baby, cry baby and make fun of me!"

236
00:12:54,659 --> 00:12:57,959
He kept complaining.

237
00:12:57,959 --> 00:13:00,059
It could've been an old friend of his

238
00:13:00,059 --> 00:13:02,459
that knew him since he was child.

239
00:13:02,459 --> 00:13:06,859
I told the police about this 20 years ago too.

240
00:13:06,859 --> 00:13:08,459
"For pedestrians and bicycles only"

241
00:13:09,459 --> 00:13:11,059
The next one we're visiting

242
00:13:11,059 --> 00:13:15,259
is the house of a victim that was killed 20 years ago too.

243
00:13:15,259 --> 00:13:17,059
He is the younger brother of the Assistant Professor

244
00:13:17,059 --> 00:13:18,359
of the science and technology department,

245
00:13:18,359 --> 00:13:19,759
Mr. Atsunori Mugita, who was killed 2 days after Mr. Bokawa,

246
00:13:19,759 --> 00:13:22,359
He was suspected because his older brother

247
00:13:22,359 --> 00:13:24,359
was covered by a huge insurance policy.

248
00:13:24,359 --> 00:13:25,959
But, no connection was found between him

249
00:13:25,959 --> 00:13:29,359
and the victim of the first case.

250
00:13:29,359 --> 00:13:31,959
What about with the lawyer in the third case?

251
00:13:31,959 --> 00:13:34,759
Of course, it seems they found no connection.

252
00:13:39,559 --> 00:13:43,659
Criminal psychologist, Mr. Doji Hiramune.

253
00:13:43,659 --> 00:13:44,859
So he makes...

254
00:13:44,859 --> 00:13:47,559
"Hidekuni Mugita (56)" -a lot of appearances on TV shows,

255
00:13:47,559 --> 00:13:50,459
but I don't like watching TV, you see.

256
00:13:50,459 --> 00:13:53,659
And, Mr. Hiramune was killed.

257
00:13:53,659 --> 00:13:57,159
By the same killer that killed your brother Atsunori.

258
00:13:58,159 --> 00:13:59,459
Aren't you shocked?

259
00:13:59,459 --> 00:14:01,759
Well, sort of.

260
00:14:01,759 --> 00:14:06,859
But, I've made up my mind to forget about that case 5 years ago

261
00:14:06,859 --> 00:14:08,959
when it expired.

